Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe governor of Anambra State, Charles Soludo, has described the death of Deputy Inspector General of Police, Joseph Egbunike, as a major loss to the state.
He said this on Saturday on his Facebook page as the late DIG is buried.
Soludo said, “The death of DIG Joseph O. Egbunike Psc. Fcna is a huge loss to our dear Anambra State.
“Today, I joined his family, friends and the good people of Onitsha to pay a deserving final respect to an illustrious son whose life was of utmost impact to humanity.”  
